main event: A witness observed three triangular-shaped white objects with small lights overhead in Handsboro, Miss. on March 21, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were described as having no sound during the observation., The sighting lasted for approximately 5 minutes., The objects were reported to be flying in two different directions: two to the northwest and one to the southeast., The witness was 15 years old at the time of the sighting., The report concluded that the objects could be aircraft flying in the area.
sighted object: three triangular-shaped white objects with small lights
witness description: a 15-year-old individual walking down the street
